
[1]revengeful

   REVENGEFUL, a. revenj'ful.

   1. full of revenge or a desire to inflict pain or evil for injury
   received; spiteful; malicious; wreaking revenge.

   If thy revengeful heart cannot forgive.

   2. Vindictive; inflicting punishment.

   May my hands never brandish more revengeful steel.
